<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1. Molecular phylogenies and morphological synapomorphies of the Helictopleurus fungicola species group A phylogenetic position of H. sicardi within Helictopleurus. Helictopleurus neoamplicollis and H. carbonarius are highlighted with colored dashed line to indicate their previous placement B COI-based phylogeny: magnification of the Helictopleurus fungicola clade and phylogenetic position of H. peyrierasi stat. rest. C synapomorphies of the Helictopleurus fungicola species group: basal pygidial ridge (BPyR); mesotarsal teeth (MsT) on the first tarsomere; parameres (P) elongated and evenly curved downward, basoventral lobes of the parameres bell shaped (BVLb); superior side of the membranous sac of the endophallus with spines (EpS); lamella copulatrix very simple (LC) D detail of the clypeal horns of the male of H. sicardi." , "Figure 4. Helictopleurus sicardi A, B major (A) and minor (B) male dorsal habitus C major male lateral habitus D female dorsal habitus (lectotype) and original labels E propleural groove (PpG) F VIII interstrial ridge (IR) G, H lateral and anterior view of the aedeagus; basoventral lobes (BVLb) I endophallus: endophallic spines (EpS); superior (SpLC) and inferior (IpLC) part of the lamella copulatrix." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/534483" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/534486" .

